The '''SFJAZZ Center''' is a music venue in the [[Hayes Valley]] neighborhood of [[San Francisco, California]], that opened in January 2013. It is considered the "first free-standing building in America built for jazz performance and education."<ref>{{cite web|title=New Jazz Center Opens In SFâ€™s Hayes Valley|url=http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/2013/01/21/new-jazz-center-opens-in-sfs-hayes-valley/|publisher=CBS San Francisco}}</ref>
The building was designed by [[Mark Cavagnero Associates]], and cost $64 million to complete. The performance space is the [[Bob Miner|Robert N. Miner]] Auditorium, with a sound system by [[Meyer Sound Laboratories]].<ref>[http://www.kqed.org/arts/music/article.jsp?essid=114967 Cy Musiker, "SFJAZZ Center Opens Tonight"], KQED, January 23, 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.npr.org/blogs/ablogsupreme/2013/01/22/170005655/the-new-sfjazz-center-as-seen-by-its-musicians Patrick Jarenwattananon, "The New SFJAZZ Center, As Seen By Its Musicians"], NPR, January 22, 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/place/article/SFJazz-Center-new-Cavagnero-landmark-4214299.php John King, "SFJazz Center - new Cavagnero landmark",] ''SF Gate'', January 23, 2013.</ref> The Center's official interior art is by [[Mark Ulriksen]],<ref>[http://www.sfjazz.org/official-illustrator]</ref> with additional murals by [[Sandow Birk]] and [[Elyse Pignolet]].<ref>[http://www.juxtapoz.com/current/sandow-birk-a-elyse-pignolet-murals-for-sfjazz-mural]</ref> It is home to SFJAZZ, a jazz music organization established in 1983. SFJAZZ has, since 1983, produced the [[San Francisco Jazz Festival]], and since 2004, the [[SFJAZZ Collective]].
